┌──────┬──┐ A -> B
│      │C │ B -> E
│  A   │  │ C -> D
│      ├──┤ D -> E
│      │D │ E -> X
├──────┤  │ X -> X
│   B  │  │ Y -> Z
├──┬───┴──┤ Z -> Z
│  │ Y    │
│E ├──────┤
├──┤ Z    │
│X │      │
└──┴──────┘

Can only go to row below.
If we can't go to a sibling row, we have to go to the sibling
row of our parents row.

  e.g. B has no sibling row, so B would need to go to ABCD's sibling
  row EXYZ, and we'll just go to the first window, E.

  X doesn't have a sibling row, and EXYZ doesn't either, so we'll
  have to handle the case of now more sibling rows, or parent sibling rows,
  grandparent sibling rows, etc.

┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│Table (column zero)                         │
│┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐│
││Row A   ┌────────────────┬───────────────┐││
