A is focused
- C0 - do all rows
-  RA - do all columns
-    C1 - do all rows
-      RC - 
-        WA - is focused, set as focused window
-      RD
-        WB - we have a focused window, so set WB as new focused window

B is focused
- C0
-   RA
-     C1
-       RC
-         WA
-       RD
-         WB - is focused, set as focused window
-     C2 - we can skip the rest of the columns, because we're not going
           side-to-side.
-   RB - We have to pass the focused window to RB from RA
-     C3
-       RG
-         WE - this is the next window, we focus here.

I think all I need to do is pass back that we've found a focused window,
and the next window in a row below should be focused. We can skip sibling
columns because they can't be below.

Couple key things were reqired:
- reset what type we're on (row/col) after processing children:
  - e.g.if we processed columns, set type back to row
- If we're processing columns and we find a focused window, set the skip
  flag, but then reset it from {skip, col} to {true, row} when we leave
  the row, otherwise columns in the row below us will be skipped.
  Basically, just skip the columns in the current row.

